  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Recruitment Intern",
  "description": "<h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><p><strong>Talent Acquisition & Sourcing</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proactively source candidates through social media, job portals, events, referrals, and partnerships</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain a strong recruitment pipeline for consultants, interns, and leadership tracks</p></li><li><p>Represent at career talks, campus events</p></li></ul><p><strong>Screening & Interview Coordination</strong></p><ul><li><p>Conduct initial candidate screening and profiling</p></li><li><p>Arrange and coordinate interviews, assessments, and follow-ups</p></li><li><p>Support directors in recruitment meetings and selection processes</p></li></ul><p><strong>Candidate Experience & Employer Branding</strong></p><ul><li><p>Be the first point of contact for candidates and deliver a premium recruitment experience</p></li><li><p>Support recruitment marketing initiatives (job posts, social content, events, branding)</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong relationships with prospects, even if they are not immediate hires</p></li></ul><p><strong>Onboarding & Recruitment Operations</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support onboarding process and documentation</p></li><li><p>Track recruitment metrics (leads, conversion, hiring rate, sources)</p></li><li><p>Continuously improve recruitment processes, scripts, and systems</p></li></ul><h2>🧠 Skills & Requirements</h2><p><strong>Must-Have</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in HR, Business, Psychology, Marketing, or related fields (or strong relevant experience)</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Confident, well-presented, and comfortable engaging people</p></li><li><p>Organised, responsive, and able to manage multiple candidates at once</p></li><li><p>High integrity and professionalism</p></li></ul><p><strong>Good to Have</strong></p><ul><li><p>Experience in recruitment, sales, talent acquisition, or education/campus hiring</p></li><li><p>Familiar with social media recruiting (Instagram, LinkedIn, TikTok, etc.)</p></li><li><p>Basic interview, screening, or profiling experience</p></li></ul><p><strong>We Value People Who Are</strong></p><ul><li><p>Results-driven and proactive</p></li><li><p>People-loving and emotionally intelligent</p></li><li><p>Growth-oriented and coachable</p></li><li><p>Able to handle rejection, pressure, and fast pace</p></li><li><p>Aligned with values of professionalism, ownership, and leadership</p></li></ul><p></p>",
